<br>
However, as a wizard myself...I remember doing the ice comet quest - which was a headache.  The person that suggested an analog between that quest and the key may not have been far off.<br>
<br>
Please, guys remember there are TEN SILVER links that are TINY.  This means that the items in question cannot be larger than TINY, and cannot be lore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufeynanthewizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FeynantheWizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 12:54:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4219.topic&index=113>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lore...</span><hr size=1> Im not argueing that the Lucid Shards are for the Vex Thal key (im still undecided right now) but:<br>
-The Lucid Shards may be lore, but each one identifies as something different, and you can hold as many Lucid Shards as you want, even if they are lore, as long as they each identify as something else.<br>
-The Lucid Shards are Tiny.<br>
<br>
My problem with them: They dont look like links. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueltain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eltain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 1:55:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4219.topic&index=114>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lucid Shards</span><hr size=1> Your point is well taken...as I recall each of the rods in the ice comet quests are like that... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uadrizzi01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>adrizzi01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 1:40:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4219.topic&index=115>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lucid Shards</span><hr size=1> found these screenshots:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.psyborg.com/screenshots.html">www.psyborg.com/screenshots.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufeynanthewizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FeynantheWizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 2:52:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4219.topic&index=116>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lucid Shards</span><hr size=1> Yes those screenshots supposedly came from a sneaky GM/Guide who visited the zone.<br>
<br>
It does look like a very interesting zone, the one thing that seems unusual to me is that it doesnt look like much of a &quot;raid&quot; zone, with places either have 10 mobs (which would be impossible to split) or having 1 mob. It looks more like a city to me.<br>
<br>
The floating Sword, Shield and Book interest me though, probably part of the main storyline in Vex Thal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usolmancer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solmancer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/02 10:04:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4219.topic&index=117>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lucid Shards</span><hr size=1> Well, it IS called the City of Shadow, and likely the place wasn't fully populated.  Heck, even Acrylia hasn't fully been populated yet, ie -  the palace.<br>
<br>
I'd say Vex Thal is going to be a combo ToV and Sleeper; even had a GM tell me it was compared to Sleeper.  So likely there will be quests given there (very high end stuff; maybe some Ancient spells too?), and likely it could be a raid zone that has repurcussions based on what you do.  Say, killing Luclin will change a lot about the zone, if not the entirety of Luclin?  Or a war starts between Akheva and Autarkic Umbrage (hinted), or whatever. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13>Quests of Norrath</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
